<h2>Solar Incentives in Miami</h2>

<p>Miami residents can take advantage of several valuable solar incentives to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Florida offers additional benefits including no state income tax on solar investments, property tax exemption on added home value from solar installations, and sales tax exemption on solar equipment purchases. FPL participates in net metering, allowing Miami homeowners to sell excess solar electricity back to the grid at retail rates, effectively using the utility grid as a battery. Additionally, Miami-Dade County offers expedited permitting for residential solar installations, reducing soft costs and installation timelines. Some Miami neighborhoods also qualify for additional rebates through local sustainability programs and PACE financing options for qualified homeowners.</p>

