<p>Selecting the right solar installer in Miami requires careful evaluation of experience with local conditions and regulatory requirements. Look for companies with proper Florida electrical contractor licenses, NABCEP-certified installers, and extensive experience with Miami-Dade County permitting processes. Top installers should offer comprehensive warranties including 25-year panel performance warranties, 10-15 year inverter warranties, and workmanship guarantees covering installation quality. Given Miami's challenging weather conditions, prioritize companies that use hurricane-rated mounting systems, corrosion-resistant materials, and have experience with concrete tile and metal roofing common in South Florida. Check Better Business Bureau ratings, online reviews, and request references from recent local installations. Reputable installers will provide detailed energy production estimates, handle all permitting and utility interconnection paperwork, and offer monitoring systems to track system performance over time.</p>

